date-'Painted at La Picaudi&Atilde;&uml;re, February 1958 - Zurich, June 1965 - Silvaplana, July 1965 - painted over October 1965',
hundertwasser_comment_ge-'Arnulf Rainer gab mir einige von ihm gemalte Bilder, die er nicht mehr brauchte, als Malgrund zum &Atilde;bermalen. Wir waren beide noch sehr arm. Mir tat es leid, da&Atilde; er Bilder wegwerfen wollte. Mir war alles &quot;Bearbeitete&quot; heilig. Ich glaubte fest, da&Atilde; bereits &quot;belebte&quot; Bilder eine Seele haben so wie Waldhumusboden, auf dem Neues besser wachsen kann. Meine &Atilde;bermalungen von Rainer-Bildern waren sozusagen ehrf&Atilde;&frac14;rchtig und haben nichts mit den sp&Atilde;&curren;teren &Atilde;bermalungen von Rainer zu tun. Es ist aber sicherlich eine eigenartige, vorahnungsvolle Transzendenz dahinter, die oft, auf unerkl&Atilde;&curren;rliche Weise in meinen Bildern vorkommt: z.B. in 606 Hana no Hana - Konrad Bayers Tod, in der Serigraphie 700 Olympisch Spiele M&Atilde;&frac14;nchen 1972, auch im Plakat Sarajewo sowie in 165 Arkadenhaus und gelber Turm.',
hundertwasser_comment_en-'Arnulf Rainer gave me some paintings he had painted which he no longer needed, to use as ground for my paintings. We were both still very poor. I was saddened that he wanted to throw paintings away. To me anything which had been &quot;worked on&quot; was sacred. I was firmly convinced that paintings which had already been &quot;given life&quot; had a soul, just like the humus soil of the forest, from which new things can grow better. My overpaintings of Rainer&#039;s paintings were reverent, so to speak, and have nothing to do with Rainer&#039;s own overpaintings later. But there is surely a strange, anticipatory transcendency behind it, which often inexplicably occurs in my pictures: e.g., in 606 Hana no Hana - The Nose-Flower - Konrad Bayer&#039;s Death, in the silkscreen print 700 Olympic Games Munich 1972, as well as in the poster 779 A Olympia and in 165 Arcade House and Yellow Tower.',
