object(paint,'577','MEIN BEITRAG F&Atilde;R &quot;LA LUNE EN RODAGE&quot;',[
id-483,
typeOfObject-'paint',
workNumber-577,
title-'MEIN BEITRAG F&Atilde;R &quot;LA LUNE EN RODAGE&quot;',
titleGerman-'MEIN BEITRAG F&Atilde;R &quot;LA LUNE EN RODAGE&quot;',
titleEnglish-'My contribution to &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;',
description-'Vienna 1953 - Paris 1959  The artist has cut into 240 small pieces 7 watercolours no. 155A, 157 and 159 from 1953 and no. 402, 410, 411, 413 and 415 from 1959 for the volume &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; edition by Carl Laszlo, Basel.  Numbered edition 150, 65 unnumbered for the artists.  The pieces from the watercolours of 1953 are about postcard size, the one from the watercolours from 1959 around 50 x 30 mm. The later are partly mounted on pieces from 1953, were though mostly glued on wrapping paper primed with chalk and PV, 220 x 150 mm and surrounded with a red and blue semi-circle.',
finishedPlace-'Paris',
year-1959,
techniqueKeyword-'Watercolour',
date-'Painted in Vienna, 1953 - Paris, 1959',
hundertwasser_comment_ge-'Mein Beitrag f&Atilde;&frac14;r &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;, Wien 1953 - Paris 1959 F&Atilde;&frac14;r das Album &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;, herausgegeben von Carl Laszlo, Basel, habe ich 7 Aquarelle, und zwar die Nummern 155A, 157 und 159 von 1953 und die Nummern 402, 410, 411, 413 und 415 von 1959, in 240 kleine St&Atilde;&frac14;cke zerschnitten und mit &quot;100 ~&quot; signiert, einen kleinen Teil mit &quot;Hundertwasser&quot; (150 St&Atilde;&frac14;ck in numerierten Ausgaben, 65 unnumeriert f&Atilde;&frac14;r die K&Atilde;&frac14;nstler). Die St&Atilde;&frac14;cke, die aus den Aquarellen von 1953 stammen, haben etwa Postkartengr&Atilde;&para;&Atilde;e. Die St&Atilde;&frac14;cke, die aus den Aquarellen von 1959 stammen, sind ungef&Atilde;&curren;hr 5 x 3 cm gro&Atilde;. Letztere sind zum Teil auf die Aquarellst&Atilde;&frac14;cke von 1953, jedoch zum gr&Atilde;&para;&Atilde;ten Teil auf wei&Atilde; grundierte Packpapierst&Atilde;&frac14;cke, ungef&Atilde;&curren;hr 22 x 15 cm gro&Atilde;, geklebt und mit einem rot-blauen Halbkreis, in Aquarell gemalt, umgeben worden. Da es sich um einen bibliophilen Beitrag handelt, anerkenne ich nur jene Exemplare, die in &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; eingeklebt sind und nicht die, die aus den Alben herausgerissen worden sind und f&Atilde;&curren;lschlich als kleinformatige Werke betrachtet werden k&Atilde;&para;nnten. 26 Exemplare dieser 240 St&Atilde;&frac14;ck z&Atilde;&curren;hlenden Ausgabe sind &Atilde;&frac14;bermalt und in Bilder umgewandelt worden. Sie tragen den Titel: &quot;Survivants de Laszlo&quot;. (aus: Kat. Kestner Gesellschaft, Hannover, 1964, S. 186) Wie bef&Atilde;&frac14;rchtet wurden meine Winzig-Kollagen aus der &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;-Edition herausgerissen, separat gerahmt und kamen als Originalbilder, die ich  dann authentifizieren mu&Atilde;te, in Auktionen.',
hundertwasser_comment_en-'My contribution to &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;, Vienna, 1953 - Paris, 1959. For the album &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;, edited by Carl Laszlo, Basel, I cut watercolours, numbers 155A, 157 and 159 of 1953 and 402, 410, 411, 413 and 415 of 1959, into 240 little pieces and signed them &quot;100 &quot; and a small number with &quot;Hundertwasser&quot; (150 copies in numbered editions, 65 non-numbered for artists). The pieces stemming from watercolours of 1953 are about the size of a postcard. The pieces from the watercolours of 1959 are about 5 &Atilde; 3 cm. The latter are in part pasted onto the watercolour pieces of 1953, but most of them are on pieces of white-primed packing paper about 22 &Atilde; 15 cm in size and with a red-and-blue watercolour semicircle around it. Since this was a bibliophile project, I only recognise the ones which are pasted into &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; and not those which have been torn out of the album and could be taken to be small-format works in their own right. 26 copies of this edition of 240 have been painted over and transformed into pictures. They are entitled Survivants de Laszlo. (from: Catalogue Kestner Gesellschaft, Hannover, 1964, p. 186) As I had feared, my tiny collages were torn out of the &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; edition, separately framed and were brought to auction as original pictures which I had to authenticate.',
information_ge-'Since this concerns a bibliophile contribution the artist recognises only the specimen in the edition &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; and does not recognise the ones outside the volume which could erroneously be taken for small size originals.  26 specimen out of the 240 pieces have been painted over and were transformed into regular paintings. These bear the title: SURVIVANTS DE LASZLO.',
literatureMonographs-'A. C. F&Atilde;&frac14;rst, Hundertwasser 1928-2000, Catalogue Raisonn&Atilde;&copy;, Cologne, 2002, Vol. II, pp. 469/470 (and c)',
literatureExhibitionCatalogues-['year'-1964, 'pointer'-'p. 186', 'city'-'Hanover']
]).

