finishedPlace-'Venice',
year-1963,
heightMm-330,
widthMm-410,
techniqueKeyword-'Mixed media',
technique-'Mixed media: watercolour, PV, oil and gold powder on several pieces of paper, mounted on hemp with PV; partly primed with chalk and PV',
date-'Painted in Vienna, April - May 1953 - Paris, 1959 - Venice, Giudecca, December 7, 1963',
hundertwasser_comment_ge-'Hier hatte ich drei kleine Aquarellst&Atilde;&frac14;cke aus &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot; zusammengeklebt. Leider hat man aus diesem Buch, das ja ausschlie&Atilde;lich als Buch gedacht ist, viele Zettel, die ich gemalt habe, herausgerissen und in den Handel gebracht, was mir furchtbar weh tut. Jedesmal, wenn man mir so einen Zettel bringt, kann man mich damit ausn&Atilde;&frac14;tzen, indem man verlangt, da&Atilde; ich ihn &Atilde;&frac14;bermale. Die Leute sagen dann: &quot;So schlechte Zettel - das kannst doch Du nicht verantworten, da&Atilde; die so herumlaufen!&quot; Und dann &Atilde;&frac14;bermale ich sie, obwohl ich furchtbar drunter leide. Das werden dann immer sch&Atilde;&para;ne Bilder. Diese Zettel stammen von fr&Atilde;&frac14;her herausgeschnittenen Aquarellen. Teils stellen sie K&Atilde;&para;pfe dar, teils kleine Muster - ich male dann dr&Atilde;&frac14;ber, und es entsteht eben etwas Neues. (aus: Hundertwasser, Buchheim Verlag, Feldafing, 1964, S. 36)',
hundertwasser_comment_en-'Here I pasted together three small watercolour pieces from &quot;La Lune en Rodage&quot;. Regrettably, many pieces I had painted were torn out of this book, which was intended exclusively as a book, and were put on the market, which greatly pains me. Every time somebody brings me such a scrap of paper, they can exploit me by asking me to paint it over. People say, &quot;What awful scraps of paper - you can&#039;t let them run around like that!&quot; And then I paint them over, even though it makes me suffer. They always turn out to be beautiful pictures. These bits of paper are from watercolours I cut up earlier. Some of them depict heads, some small patterns - I paint over them, and then something new comes about. (from: Hundertwasser, Buchheim Verlag, Feldafing, 1964, p. 36)',
information_ge-'This Painting contains four pieces of watercolours (from 157 and 159, painted in 1953), cut in 1959 for La Lune en Rodage, see 577.',
