year-1974,
heightMm-330,
widthMm-410,
techniqueKeyword-'Mixed media',
technique-'Mixed media: watercolour, egg tempera, oil, chocolate and cigarette staniol paper on parchment, primed with chalk; mounted on hemp',
date-'Painted in Venice, January 1963 - Vienna, 1964 - Venice, March 11, 1966 - after model on board the Regentag, La Goulette, Tunis, December 1973 - finished Hahns&Atilde;&curren;ge, January 20, 1974',
hundertwasser_comment_ge-'Ich malte sehr selten Akte, da das Abzeichnen des Menschen meine Kreativit&Atilde;&curren;t behindert. Dies trifft nicht f&Atilde;&frac14;r Klimt und Schiele zu. Ich hatte einen Frauenakt begonnen und wu&Atilde;te nicht, wie ich Beine, F&Atilde;&frac14;&Atilde;e, H&Atilde;&curren;nde, Br&Atilde;&frac14;ste und Kopf zu Ende malen kann. Au&Atilde;erdem kam das in Konflikt zu meiner Farben- und Formenwelt. So ist mir Valie Export, damals Waltraude, zu Hilfe gekommen und war eine Stunde mein Modell. Die seltsam gebogenen W&Atilde;&frac14;rste in der obersten und untersten Reihe sind von Hans Neuffer und mir. Manchmal lasse ich Malerfreunde an meinen Bildern etwas dazumalen, das gibt mir unerwartete, neue Impulse und Kontraste.',
hundertwasser_comment_en-'I painted nudes only very rarely, as drawing people hampers my creativity. This is not true of Klimt and Schiele. I had started a female nude and didn&#039;t know how I was to finish painting the legs, feet, hands, breasts and head. Moreover, it came into conflict with my world of colours and forms. So Valie Export, whose first name was still Waltraude at the time, helped me out and was my model for an hour. The oddly contorted sausages in the upper and lower row are by Hans Neuffer and me. Sometimes I let painter friends paint something in my pictures; that gives me unexpected new impulses and contrasts.',
